                " Laboratory at Michigan State University."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Radioactive beams were produced by fragmentation of a",
                " primary beam on a thick beryllium target. Secondary",
                " beams were magnetically analyzed in the A1900",
                " fragment separator and subsequently transported to",
                " the S800 high-resolution spectrometer"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three data sets taken with secondary beams of 26Ne,",
                " 28Mg, and 30Si at an incident mid-target energy of 83,",
                " 82, and 66 MeV/u, respectively. The secondary beam was",
                " impinged on a 375(4) mg/ cm2 self-supporting beryllium",
                " target positioned at the target position of the S800."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In all three cases presented here, the",
                " spectrograph was operated in dispersion-matched optics",
                " mode. The Segmented Germanium Array (SeGA) was",
                " positioned around the target position of the S800 to",
                " observe coincident gamma radiation. The array was",
                " arranged in a two ring configuration with 7 detectors",
                " positioned at 37 degree inclination with respect to",
                " the beam axis and 8 detectors positioned at 90 degree",
                " inclination."
              ]
            }
          ],
